article.headline: UCF 82, Liberty 58
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. -- Isaac Sosa and A.J. Tyler scored 13 points apiece to lead Central Florida past Liberty 82-58 in the first round of the UCF Holiday Classic on Tuesday night. A.J. Rompza added 12 points and Keith Clanton grabbed 14 rebounds for the Knights (8-4), who play Jacksonville in the championship game at 7 p.m. Wednesday. The Knights led by six points at halftime and went on an 8-0 run midway through the second half to seal the win. UCF, which is 5-0 at home this season, bounced back after losses to rival South Florida and No. 10 Connecticut. The Knights shot 51.9 percent from the floor for the game (28-for-54), compared to just a 33.3 mark for the Flames (21-for-63). Kyle Ohman paced the Flames (6-7) with 18 points and Antwan Burrus added 10 points. The Flames had a two-game winning streak snapped.
